gw.plugin.vendormanagement

Interface IServiceRequestMetricLimitFinderPlugin

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin, java.rmi.Remote

    public interface IServiceRequestMetricLimitFinderPlugin
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.integration.plugins.internal.InternalPlugin
    Used to find matching metric limits for service requests & determining if the existing limit values are out of date.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ServiceRequestMetricLimitValues findLimitValues(ServiceRequestMetric metric)
      Searches for a matching metric limit based on the type of metric and attributes of the service request (ie CustomerServiceTier, Tier, Service Category, Specialist Service).
      boolean limitValuesOutOfDate(ServiceRequest serviceRequest)
      Determines if the limits for a service request are out of date, generally by seeing if any of the match fields have changed, or the service request is new.

    • Method Detail

      • findLimitValues

        ServiceRequestMetricLimitValues findLimitValues(ServiceRequestMetric metric)
        Searches for a matching metric limit based on the type of metric and attributes of the service request (ie CustomerServiceTier, Tier, Service Category, Specialist Service).
        Parameters:
        metric - The metric to find limits for
        Returns:
        A ServiceRequestMetricLimitValues object holding the limit values from the matching limit, or null if no match was found.

      • limitValuesOutOfDate

        boolean limitValuesOutOfDate(ServiceRequest serviceRequest)
        Determines if the limits for a service request are out of date, generally by seeing if any of the match fields have changed, or the service request is new.
        Parameters:
        serviceRequest - The service request with the metrics and limits to check
        Returns:
        true if the limit values are out of date and need to be updated, false otherwise
